This was announced as the country kicked off its 2018 tobacco selling season in the capital, Harare. 

Government has announced that it is adding Tobacco to its programme of Command Agriculture through which capacity for local producers and beneficiation is enhanced. 

Although late rains affected the crop, Farmers are still expected to pocket more than half a billion dollars, an increase of 5.8% in volumes. Nthakoana Ngatane compiled this report… --SABC--